news.title: Singapore sovereign fund GIC invests Rs 400 crore more in Phoenix Mills' joint venture
news.para: The investment is the second tranche of investment under the strategic partnership between GIC and India’s largest retail-led mixed-use asset developer and operator to set up a joint venture to develop, own and operate retail-led, mixed-use developments across India.

news.title: Prayagraj authority opens window for online application for PMAY houses
news.para: “The window for the online application for the allotment of these PMAY houses commenced from Thursday and would be open for a period of one month,” said PDA vice-chairman Arvind Chauhan.

news.title: No TS-1 certificate if vacant plots turn dump yards: Ludhiana civic body chief
news.para: Besides, MC officials will also challan plot owners, who are accountable to keep their plots clean. The owners of such plots will be directed to get a boundary wall constructed so that people could not use the area to dump garbage.

news.title: Housing complexes in Kolkata try to decipher groundwater board notification
news.para: As per the updated guidelines by the ministry of Jal Shakti to regulate extraction of groundwater, it has been made mandatory for new and existing industries, group housing societies and private water supply tankers to get a NOC for withdrawal of groundwater.

news.title: Recover penalty for violation of building bylaws: Ludhiana civic body chief
news.para: ​In last year, the building branch officials issued more than 7,000 challans for violation in the building construction but only 1,300 were assessed and challan amount was recovered from the defaulters.

news.title: Start online system for submission of building plans from July 1: Nashik civic body
news.para: Pawar told TOI that the process of submission and approval of the building plans for all the small and big projects will be online from July 1. He has already given instructions to the town planning officials to start the online process, he said.

news.title: Hyderabad development body's land auctions fetch Rs 137 crore
news.para: In the land auctions conducted by the Hyderabad Metropolitan Development Authority (HMDA) on Thursday, one plot in Turkamjal was sold for Rs 62,500 per sq yard against the upset price Rs 40,000.

news.title: About 250 flats in upscale colonies of Gurugram violated building norms: DTCP
news.para: Most of these properties are in DLF 1-3, Sushant Lok-1, South City 1 and 2, Malibu Towne, Suncity and Mayfield Garden.

news.title: Indiabulls Housing raises $100 million via offshore loan from SBI
news.para: The fundraise, which comes amid volatile market conditions, is expected to help the home financier expand into lending for the low-income – or affordable - housing segment, one of the people said. IBHF has over 151 branches in India

news.title: Delhi government discontinues rebate on circle rates
news.para: ​The decision was taken by the government as as the impact of the Covid pandemic has subsided and the economy of the city is recovering fast, they said.

news.title: Godrej Capital to offer flexi-repayments, longer tenor loans against property for SMEs
news.para: ​The non-bank financier, which is among the youngest of the lending companies having entered in late 2020, will let borrowers from the Small and Medium Enterprises (SME) segment 'design' their own earnest monthly installments, as per an official statement.

news.title: Don't harass citizens with 'pending' issues of sale deed: Gujarat revenue department
news.para: In the latest notification dated June 28, the superintendent of stamps, Jenu Devan, has instructed its officers to stop registering any sale deed if the supporting documents are found to be incomplete.

news.title: Over 500 illegal constructions demolished in three months: Bihar minister
news.para: He said the bulldozer will continue to work against illegal setups in the state and asked the MLCs to lodge a complaint to the circle officer, if they know about any such encroachment on government land.

news.title: PNB Housing to seek shareholders' nod next month to raise Rs 12,000 crore in debt
news.para: The housing finance company promoted by the city-headquartered state-owned lender Punjab National Bank (PNB) is scheduled to convene its annual general meeting (AGM) next month on July 26.

news.title: UltraTech Cement paying for Russian coal in Chinese yuan
news.para: UltraTech is bringing in 157,000 tonnes of coal from Russian producer SUEK that loaded on the bulk carrier MV Mangas from the Russian Far East port of Vanino, the document showed.
